      <h2>Tips for the Best Experience</h2>
      <p>Take seasickness medication the night before and the morning of — even calm-looking seas can be rougher offshore. Bring sunscreen (the boat deck has no shade), a hat, a light jacket (sea breezes are cooler than expected) and a waterproof bag for your camera. A camera with a 200mm+ zoom lens dramatically improves whale photography. Sit toward the front of the boat for better sightings. Sightings, while highly likely, are never guaranteed — the ocean is wild and unpredictable.</p>
